ll,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThyroid follicular adenoma is a benign neoplasm with distinct histological features. The key characteristic is a \u003Cstrong\u003Ewell-defined fibrous capsule\u003C/strong\u003E that completely surrounds the lesion. The presence of \u003Cstrong\u003Emultiple scattered nodules\u003C/strong\u003E is more typical of multinodular goitre. \u003Cstrong\u003ECapsular invasion\u003C/strong\u003E is a defining feature of follicular carcinoma, not adenoma. \u003Cstrong\u003ENuclear ground glass appearance\u003C/strong\u003E is characteristic of papillary thyroid carcinoma. \u003Cstrong\u003ELymphocytic infiltration\u003C/strong\u003E is typically seen in autoimmune thyroiditis.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EOther features of follicular adenomas include:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E    \u003Cli\u003ESolitary nodular growth pattern\u003C/li\u003E    \u003Cli\u003EUniform follicular cells\u003C/li\u003E    \u003Cli\u003EVariable follicle sizes\u003C/li\u003E    \u003Cli\u003EAbsence of invasion into surrounding tissue\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Follicular adenomas are benign thyroid neoplasms characterized by a well-defined fibrous capsule and uniform follicular cells","Follicular adenomas typically present as solitary, encapsulated nodules with variable follicle sizes"],"references":["Shah JP. Thyroid carcinoma: epidemiology, histology, and diagnosis. Clin Adv Hematol Oncol. 2015 Apr;13(4 Suppl 4):3-6. PMID: 26430868; PMCID: PMC5526593","Kitahara CM, Schneider AB. Epidemiology of Thyroid Cancer. Cancer Epidemiol Biomarkers Prev. 2022 Jul 1;31(7):1284-1297. doi: 10.1158/1055-9965.EPI-21-1440. PMID: 35775227; PMCID: PMC9473679","Boucai L, Zafereo M, Cabanillas ME. Thyroid Cancer: A Review. JAMA. 2024 Feb 6;331(5):425-435. doi: 10.1001/jama.2023.26348. PMID: 38319329","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sci